> **DOCUMENT 1 --- CERTIFICATE OF FORMATION**

**State of Texas --- Certificate of Formation**

*Texas Secretary of State Form 205 \| Texas Business Organizations Code
(TBOC) § 101.051*

Filed with the Texas Secretary of State to formally organize Provenarc
Group LLC as a Texas limited liability company. The information below
constitutes the public filing record and establishes the Company\'s
legal existence under Title 3, Chapter 101 of the Texas Business
Organizations Code.

**Article 1 --- Entity Name**

The name of the filing entity is:

**PROVENARC GROUP LLC**

The name \"Provenarc Group LLC\" is the exclusive legal name under which
the Company shall conduct its affairs and execute all contracts,
agreements, and filings. The Company may conduct business under
registered trade names (\"d/b/a\") if separately registered with the
Texas Secretary of State, provided that any such trade names are
authorized by the Co-Managing Members in writing.

**Article 2 --- Entity Type**

The filing entity is a Limited Liability Company (LLC) organized under
the Texas Business Organizations Code, Title 3, Chapter 101. As a
limited liability company, the personal assets of each Member are
shielded from the debts and liabilities of the Company except to the
extent required by applicable law or as expressly agreed by a Member in
writing.

**Article 3 --- Registered Agent and Registered Office**

The Company shall maintain a registered agent authorized to conduct
business in the State of Texas at all times, as required by TBOC §
5.201. The registered agent\'s consent to serve is required and shall be
documented in the Company\'s organizational records. The initial
registered office address is:

**Registered Agent Name:**
\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_

**Street Address (No P.O. Box):**
\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_

**City, State, ZIP Code:**
\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_

Any change in registered agent or registered office shall be filed with
the Texas Secretary of State (Form 401) and shall not require amendment
to this Certificate. The registered agent shall be responsible for
accepting service of process on behalf of the Company during regular
business hours.

**Article 4 --- Principal Office and Place of Business**

The principal office and primary place of business of the Company is:

**100 Park Lane, Suite 11**

**Kerrville, Texas 78028**

The principal office may be relocated by written consent of the
Co-Managing Members, and such change shall be reflected in the
Company\'s records and reported in the annual Public Information Report
filed with the Texas Comptroller.

**Article 5 --- Governing Documents**

The Company shall be governed by a Company Agreement (Operating
Agreement) adopted by the Members in accordance with TBOC § 101.052. The
Company Agreement constitutes a binding contract among the Members and
shall govern: (i) the rights and obligations of the Members inter se;
(ii) the management structure of the Company; (iii) allocation of
profits, losses, and distributions; (iv) transfer restrictions on
Membership Interests; (v) dissolution and winding-up procedures; and
(vi) all other matters pertaining to the internal affairs of the Company
not otherwise mandated by statute. In the event of any conflict between
this Certificate and the Company Agreement, the Company Agreement shall
control as between the Members, and this Certificate shall control as to
third parties.

**Article 6 --- Management Structure**

The Company shall be MEMBER-MANAGED. Management authority is vested
jointly in the Members as Co-Managing Members, each possessing equal
authority in proportion to their equal Membership Interests. The initial
Co-Managing Members are:

