**Article 9 --- Member Liability**

Pursuant to TBOC § 101.114, no Member shall be liable for any debt,
obligation, or liability of the Company or for any act or omission by
any other Member, solely by reason of being a Member of the Company or
by acting in the capacity of a Member. This limitation shall apply to
all debts, obligations, and liabilities of the Company whether arising
in contract, tort, or otherwise.

**Article 10 --- Duration**

The Company shall have perpetual existence unless dissolved in
accordance with the Company Agreement and the Texas Business
Organizations Code. The existence of the Company commences on the date
this Certificate is filed and accepted by the Texas Secretary of State.

