> **DOCUMENT 3 --- INTELLECTUAL PROPERTY & ASSET ASSIGNMENT AGREEMENT**

**Assignment to Provenarc Group LLC**

This Intellectual Property and Asset Assignment Agreement (this
\"Assignment\") is entered into as of the date last signed below,
between Dalton Montes and Daniel Wiglesworth (individually and
collectively, \"Assignors\") and Provenarc Group LLC, a Texas limited
liability company with its principal office at 100 Park Lane, Suite 11,
Kerrville, Texas 78028 (the \"Company\" or \"Assignee\").

**RECITALS**

WHEREAS, the Assignors are the founding Members and Co-Managing Members
of the Company and have developed, conceived, or acquired certain
intellectual property, brand assets, software, methodologies, and
tangible assets in connection with the establishment of the Provenarc
enterprise;

WHEREAS, the Company is intended to serve as the parent holding entity
for all Provenarc-branded business ventures, including the aviation
subsidiary Provenarc Aero Solutions, and as such, all intellectual
property and core business assets shall be owned at the Company level to
preserve the structural integrity of the enterprise and provide maximum
protection of asset value;

WHEREAS, the Assignors desire to assign, transfer, and convey all right,
title, and interest in such intellectual property and assets to the
Company in exchange for capital contribution credit as set forth herein;

NOW, THEREFORE, in consideration of the mutual covenants,
representations, and agreements contained herein, and for other good and
valuable consideration, the receipt and sufficiency of which are hereby
acknowledged, the parties agree as follows:

**ARTICLE 1 --- ASSIGNMENT OF INTELLECTUAL PROPERTY**

**Section 1.1 --- Scope of IP Assignment**

Each Assignor hereby irrevocably and unconditionally assigns, transfers,
conveys, and sets over to the Company, its successors and assigns, all
of Assignor\'s right, title, and interest, worldwide and in perpetuity,
in and to the following intellectual property and related rights
(collectively, the \"Assigned IP\"):

-   The trade name and brand identity \"Provenarc Group\" and all
    associated visual identity elements

-   The trade name and brand identity \"Provenarc Aero Solutions\" and
    all associated visual identity elements

-   The Provenarc color system (deep navy #0D2240 and amber gold
    #C89B2A) as applied to business branding

-   All trademarks, service marks, trade dress, and logos, whether
    registered or unregistered, including all applications for
    registration and the goodwill associated therewith

-   All domain names registered or to be registered in connection with
    any Provenarc entity, including rights under the Uniform Domain-Name
    Dispute-Resolution Policy

-   The RecordVault software platform: all source code, object code,
    documentation, APIs, user interface designs, database schemas, and
    derivative works

-   All proprietary service delivery methodologies, aviation records
    digitization protocols, quality control frameworks, and operational
    procedures

-   All client-facing documents including service agreement templates,
    intake forms, pricing schedules, and scope-of-work templates

-   All marketing and promotional materials including website content,
    copy, photography, video content, brochures, presentations, and
    social media assets

-   All client data, prospect lists, partner contact databases, and
    market research

-   All business plans, financial models, partnership proposals, and
    strategic planning documents

-   Any and all trade secrets, confidential business information, and
    know-how relating to the Company\'s operations

-   Any patent applications or patentable inventions conceived in
    connection with the Company\'s business

-   All renewals, extensions, and foreign equivalents of any of the
    foregoing

**Section 1.2 --- Rights Included in Assignment**

The assignment under Section 1.1 includes, without limitation: (i) all
rights to register, renew, maintain, enforce, and defend the Assigned IP
in any jurisdiction; (ii) all claims for past, present, and future
infringement, misappropriation, or other violation of the Assigned IP;
(iii) all royalties, license fees, and other sums payable with respect
to the Assigned IP; and (iv) all rights to create derivative works,
modify, adapt, or build upon the Assigned IP.

**Section 1.3 --- No Retained Rights**

Upon execution of this Assignment, neither Assignor shall retain any
ownership rights in the Assigned IP except as expressly licensed back by
the Company pursuant to the Company Agreement or a separate written
license agreement. Each Assignor\'s use of the Assigned IP following
this Assignment shall be solely in their capacity as Co-Managing Member
of the Company or pursuant to an express written license.

**Section 1.4 --- Further Assurances**

Each Assignor agrees, at the Company\'s request and expense, to execute,
acknowledge, and deliver any additional instruments, certificates,
assignments, or other documents, and to perform any acts necessary or
useful to perfect and maintain the Company\'s ownership of the Assigned
IP in any jurisdiction, including USPTO trademark applications and
assignments, U.S. Copyright Office registrations, domain name registrar
transfer documents, and any filings required under applicable state or
foreign law.

**ARTICLE 2 --- ASSIGNMENT OF TANGIBLE ASSETS**

