> **DOCUMENT 4 --- MEMBER RESOLUTION: SUBSIDIARY AUTHORIZATION**

**Written Consent in Lieu of Meeting --- Provenarc Aero Solutions**

This Written Consent in Lieu of Meeting (this \"Resolution\") is adopted
by all Members of Provenarc Group LLC, a Texas limited liability company
(the \"Company\"), effective as of the date last signed below, pursuant
to Texas Business Organizations Code § 101.357 and Article 5, Section
5.8 of the Company Agreement. This Resolution has the same force and
effect as a vote taken at a duly called and held meeting of the Members.

The undersigned Members, Dalton Montes and Daniel Wiglesworth, being all
of the Members of Provenarc Group LLC, hereby unanimously consent to and
adopt the following resolutions:

**Resolution 1 --- Formation and Organization of Provenarc Aero
Solutions**

RESOLVED, that the Company is hereby authorized and directed to form
Provenarc Aero Solutions as a Texas limited liability company, to be
wholly owned by Provenarc Group LLC. Both Co-Managing Members are
jointly authorized and directed to: (i) execute and file a Certificate
of Formation for Provenarc Aero Solutions with the Texas Secretary of
State; (ii) adopt a Company Agreement for Provenarc Aero Solutions that
is consistent with this Resolution and the Provenarc Group LLC Company
Agreement; (iii) obtain a separate EIN for Provenarc Aero Solutions from
the IRS; (iv) open one or more bank accounts in the name of Provenarc
Aero Solutions; and (v) take all other organizational actions necessary
to complete the formation of Provenarc Aero Solutions.

**Resolution 2 --- Business Purpose and Authorized Activities of
Provenarc Aero Solutions**

RESOLVED, that Provenarc Aero Solutions is authorized to engage in the
following business activities as the aviation services operating
subsidiary of the Company:

-   Aircraft records digitization, logbook scanning, and digital
    archiving services

-   Aviation document consulting, compliance analysis, and records
    organization services

-   Airworthiness Directive (AD) compliance auditing and reporting

-   FAA Form 8130-3 extraction, verification, and parts traceability
    database services

-   Pre-buy inspection records support and digital closing packet
    preparation

-   Estate and probate aircraft records assessment and digitization

-   Fleet compliance services for Part 135 operators and corporate
    flight departments

-   On-site and concierge records scanning services throughout the Texas
    Hill Country and nationwide

-   Subscription-based maintenance records updating services

-   White-label scanning services for aircraft brokers and MRO
    facilities

-   Physical logbook restoration, rebinding, and archival preservation
    services

-   Licensing of the RecordVault software platform to third parties
    (subject to Company approval)

RESOLVED FURTHER, that Provenarc Aero Solutions shall operate
exclusively within this authorized scope. Any material expansion of
scope requires prior written approval of both Co-Managing Members of the
Company.

**Resolution 3 --- IP License to Provenarc Aero Solutions**

RESOLVED, that the Company hereby grants to Provenarc Aero Solutions a
non-exclusive, non-transferable, royalty-free license to use the
following IP Assets solely in connection with its authorized aviation
services operations:

-   The trade name \"Provenarc Aero Solutions\" and associated brand
    elements

-   The Provenarc deep navy and amber gold brand identity system
    (typography, colors, logo templates)

-   The RecordVault software platform for client-facing deployments

-   All proprietary scanning protocols, aviation records digitization
    methodologies, and quality control frameworks

-   All service agreement templates, client intake forms, pricing
    schedules, and work product templates

-   All marketing materials developed for aviation services

RESOLVED FURTHER, that this IP license: (i) does not transfer any
ownership of IP Assets; (ii) is automatically suspended or revoked upon
dissolution of Provenarc Aero Solutions or upon written notice from both
Co-Managing Members; (iii) does not permit Provenarc Aero Solutions to
sublicense any IP Assets without written approval from both Co-Managing
Members; (iv) shall be subject to a written Inter-Company License
Agreement to be executed between the Company and Provenarc Aero
Solutions within sixty (60) days of the subsidiary\'s formation; and (v)
shall be reflected on the Company\'s balance sheet as an inter-company
license at arm\'s-length terms.

**Resolution 4 --- Asset Use Authorization**

RESOLVED, that Provenarc Aero Solutions is authorized to use the
tangible assets listed in the IP & Asset Assignment Agreement for
operational purposes, subject to the following conditions: (i) all
assets shall remain titled in the name of Provenarc Group LLC; (ii)
Provenarc Aero Solutions shall maintain the assets in good working
condition and promptly report any damage, loss, or malfunction to the
Co-Managing Members; (iii) any use of assets for purposes outside
Provenarc Aero Solutions\' authorized activities requires advance
written approval; (iv) upon dissolution, all assets shall be returned to
the Company or disposed of pursuant to Company direction; and (v) an
Equipment Use Agreement documenting these terms shall be executed
between the Company and Provenarc Aero Solutions within sixty (60) days.

**Resolution 5 --- Financial Structure and Banking**

RESOLVED, that Provenarc Aero Solutions shall: (i) maintain one or more
dedicated bank accounts in the name \"Provenarc Aero Solutions\"
separate from any Company or Member accounts; (ii) keep complete and
accurate books and records separate from the Company\'s books and
records; (iii) not commingle its funds with the Company\'s funds or with
any Member\'s personal funds; (iv) invoice all clients in the name of
Provenarc Aero Solutions; (v) pay all operating expenses from its own
accounts; and (vi) make distributions or transfers to the Company only
pursuant to written inter-company transfer documentation approved by
both Co-Managing Members.

**Resolution 6 --- Management of Provenarc Aero Solutions**

RESOLVED, that Dalton Montes and Daniel Wiglesworth shall serve as joint
Co-Managing Members of Provenarc Aero Solutions with equal management
authority, consistent with their equal ownership through Provenarc Group
LLC. All major decisions of Provenarc Aero Solutions --- including
entering contracts exceeding \$5,000, hiring employees, incurring debt,
and making distributions to the Company --- shall require the written
consent of both Co-Managing Members. Day-to-day operational decisions
may be made by either Co-Managing Member individually within the
parameters established in the Company\'s approved operating budget.

**Resolution 7 --- Inter-Company Agreements Required**

RESOLVED, that both Co-Managing Members are directed to negotiate and
execute the following inter-company agreements between Provenarc Group
LLC and Provenarc Aero Solutions within ninety (90) days of the
subsidiary\'s formation:

5.  Inter-Company IP License Agreement --- documenting the IP license
    granted under Resolution 3, including permitted use scope, term,
    termination rights, and any applicable royalty or licensing fee

6.  Equipment Use Agreement --- documenting the terms under which
    Provenarc Aero Solutions may use assets owned by the Company,
    including any use fee or maintenance obligations

7.  Shared Services Agreement (if applicable) --- documenting any
    administrative, accounting, or support services provided by the
    Company to the subsidiary, and the basis for any cost allocation

8.  Inter-Company Loan Agreement (if applicable) --- if the Company
    provides financing to the subsidiary, documenting the principal,
    interest rate, repayment terms, and security, if any

**Resolution 8 --- Future Subsidiaries**

RESOLVED, that the Co-Managing Members are authorized to propose the
formation of additional subsidiaries under the Provenarc Group LLC
umbrella --- including, without limitation, any Provenarc Marine,
Provenarc Autos & Classics, or technology subsidiary --- subject to the
unanimous written consent of both Members as required by the Company
Agreement. Any future subsidiary shall be organized under substantially
the same structural principles established in this Resolution.

**Resolution 9 --- Annual Review of Subsidiary Authorization**

RESOLVED, that the Co-Managing Members shall annually review the status,
performance, and compliance of Provenarc Aero Solutions and any other
Subsidiaries, and shall document the results of such review in writing
as part of the Company\'s annual business review required under Section
5.9 of the Company Agreement.

**CERTIFICATION --- UNANIMOUS WRITTEN CONSENT**

